{"word":"H5091 - נָהָה - nâhâh - naw-haw' - Lament","slug":"H5091","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נָהָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nâhâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>naw-haw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Lament"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05D4;&#x05D4; - na&#x0302;ha&#x0302;h</b> - <i>naw-haw'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>groan</i>, that is, <i>bewail</i>; hence (through the idea of <i>crying</i> aloud) to <i>assemble</i> (as if on proclamation): - lament, wail."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5092\">H5092</a>, <a href=\"#/H5093\">H5093</a>, <a href=\"#/H5204\">H5204</a>"}]}